.TH "ZAPPING" "1" 
.SH "NAME" 
zapping \(em  a TV viewer for the Gnome environment. 
.SH "SYNOPSIS" 
.PP 
\fBzapping\fP [\fB-b, --bpp\fP\fI[=BPP]\fP]  [\fB-d, --debug\fP]  [\fB--no-vbi\fP]  [\fB-n, --tunerless-norm\fP\fI[=NORM]\fP]  [\fB--device\fP\fI[=DEVICE]\fP]  [\fB-v, --no-xv\fP]  [\fB--dword-align\fP]  [\fB-c, --command\fP\fI[=CMD]\fP]  [\fB-z, --no-zsfb\fP]  [\fB-y, --yuv-format\fP\fI[=PIXFORMAT]\fP]  [\fB--console-errors\fP]  
.SH "DESCRIPTION" 
.PP 
\fBzapping\fP is a TV viewer, so displaying TV is 
its main goal. Nevertheless, there are a number of things that can be 
done to a image stream, and Zapping provides a way to do them, you 
just need a plug-in that fits your particular needs. If such a plug-in 
doesn't exist, you are encouraged to write one. 
.SH "OPTIONS" 
.IP "\fB-b\fP           \fB--bpp=BPP\fP         " 10 
Color depth of the X display. It is possible that, when using a
TrueColor (24 or 32 bpp) mode, you get a very distorted image that
spreads all around the desktop. This usually means that \fBZapping\fP
couldn't guess correctly the screen depth, this option will tell it
which depth is the correct one.
.IP "\fB-d\fP           \fB--debug\fP         " 10 
Set debug messages on. Always use this flag when sending bug reports,
it dumps lots of useful info.
.IP "\fB-n\fP           \fB--tunerless-norm=NORM\fP         " 10 
Set the default standard/norm for tunerless inputs.
.IP "\fB--device=DEVICE\fP         " 10 
Video device to use. 
.IP "\fB-v\fP           \fB--no-xv\fP         " 10 
Disable XVideo extension support. 
.IP "\fB--dword-align\fP" 10 
Force dword aligning of the overlay window. Can help when the image
is distorted at certain sizes but looks fine at others.
.IP "\fB-c\fP           \fB--command=CMD\fP         " 10 
.RS
Execute the given command and exit. Currently, just the
\fBset_channel\fP command is implemented, but this will be a full
featured batch mode in the future. This is useful for tuning the
device before using an application that doesn't allow tuning, the
usage is:
.P
zapping -c="set_channel BBC"
.RE
.IP "\fB-z\fP           \fB--no-zsfb\fP         " 10 
Do not call
.IR zapping_setup_fb "(1)"
on startup.
.IP "\fB-y\fP           \fB--yuv-format=PIXFORMAT\fP         " 10 
Pixformat for XVideo capture mode [YUYV | YVU420].
.IP "\fB--console-errors\fP" 10 
Redirect the error messages to the console, useful for sending bug
reports.
